any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Our curators review genetic and experimental data in the scientific literature to identify genes in which pathogenic variants cause disease.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Laboratories may use this type of information when deciding which genes to include in clinical testing panels.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Clinicians may use this type of information when interpreting test results for their patients.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.55

nodes.html: Dosage Sensitivity

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • The dosage sensitivity curation process collects evidence supporting or refuting haploinsufficiency (loss) and triplosensitivity (gain) as mechanisms for disease for genes and larger genomic regions.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Laboratories and clinicians may use this information when interpreting the clinical significance of variants involving loss or gain of genomic material, such as those identified by chromosomal microarray (CMA).

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.55

nodes.html: Variant Pathogenicity

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • The variant curation process combines clinical, genetic, population, and functional evidence with expert review to classify variants according to ACMG/AMP guidelines.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Result of variant curation are deposited in ClinVar for community access.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Laboratories and clinicians may use ClinGen’s variant curation tools to evaluate evidence for a variant that has not yet undergone expert review, or has a discrepancy in classification that requires resolution.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.55

nodes.html: Clinical Actionability

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Certain genetic conditions have medical interventions that can delay symptoms, prevent disease, result in earlier detection, etc.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • The actionability curation process evaluates availability of effective medical interventions, accounting for the chance the outcome will happen, the severity of the condition to be avoided, and the risks associated with the intervention.

any.message: Element has sufficient color contrast of 4.68

nodes.html: • Decision makers may use this information to decide which secondary finding results to report back to patients.

nodes.html: • Our curators review genetic and experimental data in the scientific literature to identify genes in which pathogenic variants cause disease.

nodes.html: <ul>

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • The dosage sensitivity curation process collects evidence supporting or refuting haploinsufficiency (loss) and triplosensitivity (gain) as mechanisms for disease for genes and larger genomic regions.

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • Laboratories and clinicians may use this information when interpreting the clinical significance of variants involving loss or gain of genomic material, such as those identified by chromosomal microarray (CMA).

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • Result of variant curation are deposited in ClinVar for community access.

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • Laboratories and clinicians may use ClinGen’s variant curation tools to evaluate evidence for a variant that has not yet undergone expert review, or has a discrepancy in classification that requires resolution.

nodes.html: • Certain genetic conditions have medical interventions that can delay symptoms, prevent disease, result in earlier detection, etc.

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • The actionability curation process evaluates availability of effective medical interventions, accounting for the chance the outcome will happen, the severity of the condition to be avoided, and the risks associated with the intervention.

any.message: All page content is contained by landmarks

nodes.html: • Decision makers may use this information to decide which secondary finding results to report back to patients.
